TYPOLOGIES OF UNNOTICED

I photographed this series between 2012 and 2014 in my hometown. Rather than the familiar historic landmarks, I focused on the often-overlooked layer of everyday architecture: utilitarian structures whose geometry, colour and surface detail form an unintended but compelling aesthetic. The project highlights a visual language that usually remains unnoticed in the cityâ€™s routine infrastructure.

item.title: About me
item.dc:creator: Miki
item.content:encoded:
Through my lens, I seek to unravel the captivating stories that unfold in the heart of the city, showcasing the dynamic interplay of light, shadows, and the vibrant energy that defines urban living.
